The Competition Commission has made it clear it will continue to closely watch the price volatility of essential food items. eNCA speaks to Thulani Mandiriza of the Competition Commission. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Competition Commission will closely monitor prices of essential food items. It says businesses that increase prices need to justify their actions. READ: Food costs continue to rise: Household Affordability Index The commission is appealing to the public to be their eyes and ears. "There are many ways we monitor, but the consumers have to be involved and can alert the commission on the prices if they are unjustifiable," said Thulani Mandiriza. "There are global and external factors. And we need to check if there are no opportunistic behaviours. The problem of food is very concerning for food producers, and this also compounds some of the factors that we're seeing."